cs.NI, cs.DC, cs.DS, cs.SY, cs.IT. 

The paper discusses a protocol for termination detection in cognitive radio networks, which involves distributed systems and wireless communication. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). The paper also involves computations on multiple channels and maintaining a logical structure, which falls under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). The protocol also involves detecting the presence of licensed users, which falls under cs.SY (Systems and Control) and cs.IT (Information Theory).
